  schema:name "Introduction to the Therapeutic Relationship" ;
  schema:description "An overview of the therapeutic alliance as the strongest predictor of psychotherapy outcome, covering its three components (goals, tasks, bond), and the mechanisms through which the relationship itself heals: corrective emotional experience, internalization, co-regulation, and rupture-repair." ;
